name: Airbnb
description: An online platform for listing, discovering, and booking unique accommodations around the world. It allows users to rent out their homes or spare rooms to travelers.An online platform for listing, discovering, and booking unique accommodations around the world.

name: Apple
description: A multinational technology company known for designing and producing consumer electronics, software, and online services. Its most famous products include the iPhone, iPad, Mac computers, and the iOS operating system.

name: Netflix
description: A leading streaming platform providing a wide array of movies, TV shows, and original content. Netflix services can be accessed from numerous devices, including TVs, computers, and mobile devices.

name: Uber
description: A ride-sharing platform that connects drivers and passengers through a smartphone app. It also offers food delivery services through Uber Eats. Instagram: A photo and video sharing social networking service, which allows users to upload content and share it with followers or with a select group of friends. It also offers features like filters, stories, and IGTV.

name: Instagram
description: A photo and video sharing social networking platform, which allows users to upload content and share it with followers or with a select group of friends. It also offers features like filters, stories, and IGTV.

name: Spotify
description: A digital music, podcast, and video streaming service that provides access to millions of songs and other content from artists globally. It has transformed the way people access and enjoy music and podcasts, making it an integral part of the modern digital entertainment landscape.

name: Instacart
description: An online grocery delivery service where users can order from their favorite local stores and have their groceries delivered to their door.

name: Meta
description: Formerly known as Facebook Inc., Meta is a technology conglomerate with a focus on developing the future of virtual reality and social networking. It's also the parent company of Instagram, WhatsApp, and Oculus VR.

name: Google
description: A multinational technology company specializing in internet-related services and products, including search, online advertising technologies, cloud computing, software, and hardware.

name: Delivery Hero
description: An online food-delivery service based in Berlin, Germany, operating in over 40 countries globally. It partners with over 500,000 restaurants.

name: Pinterest
description: Pinterest is a social media platform that allows users to discover and save ideas through visual content, creating personalized collections of inspiration.

name: Shopify
description: An ecommerce platform that allows businesses to set up online stores and sell their products. It also offers services like payments, marketing, shipping, and customer engagement tools.

name: Typeform
description: A Barcelona-based online software company specializing in online form building and online surveys. Its main software creates dynamic forms based on user interaction.

name: DigitalOcean
description: A cloud infrastructure provider offering scalable compute platforms with web servers, storage, and networking capabilities.

name: PayPal
description: An online payment system supporting money transfers, often serving as an electronic alternative to traditional paper methods like checks and money orders.

name: Stripe
description: A financial technology company that provides a range of payment processing services for online and mobile businesses.

name: Glovo
description: A Spanish quick-commerce startup that operates an app-based platform for delivering goods, including restaurant meals, groceries, and other items.

name: Twitter
description: A social networking platform where users post and interact with messages known as "tweets." It's widely used for public communication and broadcasting short messages.

name: Snap
description: The parent company of Snapchat, a multimedia messaging app popular among younger demographics for its disappearing messages and augmented reality features.

name: Red Hat
description: A software company providing open-source software products to the enterprise community. Red Hat was acquired by IBM in 2019.

name: Expedia
description: An online travel agency where users can book airline tickets, hotel reservations, car rentals, cruises, and vacation packages.

name: Tidal
description: A music streaming platform owned by artists that offers high-fidelity, CD-quality music, and high-resolution video to members.

name: Slack
description: A channel-based messaging platform that allows teams to communicate and collaborate in a shared workspace.

name: Figma
description: A cloud-based design tool used for interface design, prototyping, and collaboration. It's commonly used by UI and UX designers.

name: Lyft
description: A ride-hailing company offering car rides, scooters, and a bicycle-sharing system. Lyft operates in the U.S. and some parts of Canada.
